        "management": "High AG: MUDPILES (methanol, uremia, DKA, propylene glycol, infection/iron, lactic, ethylene glycol, salicylates). Treat underlying cause. Give bicarb only if pH <7.1 or severe. Normal AG: diarrhea, RTA. Correct cause, bicarb loss replacement."
